Coast-based musician Nyota Ndogo is giving a helping hand to the less privileged during this pandemic and as her ‘sadaka’ during Ramadhan. Nyota Ndogo is collecting funds from fans and well-wishers to help needy families. She thanked her fans and urged them to continue supporting the less fortunate. “Joining my live performance for the main purpose being to support the needy during this coronavirus pandemic, it marked a significant Blessing and Love that you got for me and other fellow human beings. I appreciate. Allah Ibarik,” she wrote. She shared a photo with an elderly man, whom she said is needy and has no family. Nyota Ndogo joins many other celebrities who have been helping people out like Akothee, Stivo Simple Boy and Diamond Platnumz.